Cisco Quiet Mode

Quiet-mode is a setting you can implement which denies all connection to the device other than console access.  The quiet-mode access-list are those IPs that are still permitted to access the device during the quiet-mode duration.

ssh connection refused after a default of 5 failed attepts

This ia factory default ACL that needs some configuring since IOS 12.3

check VTY line for the following ACL (+ AUX lines too)

"Access-class "sl_def_acl_in"
when turned off this acl disappears

show login displays if quiet mode is enabled or not

(config) no login block-for
removes quiet mode 
